---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy | Hristijan Najcheski"
  description="Cookie policy for hristijannajcheski.com — what cookies and local storage we use, why, and how to control them."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-header-content">
        <span class="section-label">Legal</span>
        <h1>Cookie <span class="text-gradient">Policy</span></h1>
        <p>Last updated: 24 April 2026</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="policy-content">

        <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
        <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your web browser when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work, improve user experience, and provide information to site owners. Related technologies include <strong>local storage</strong>, which serves a similar purpose but is not sent to the server with each request.</p>

        <h2>Cookies and storage we use</h2>
        <p>This website is designed to be lightweight and privacy-friendly. We use minimal cookies and storage:</p>

        <table class="policy-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Name</th>
              <th>Type</th>
              <th>Purpose</th>
              <th>Duration</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>theme</code></td>
              <td>Local storage</td>
              <td>Remembers your light/dark theme preference so the site loads with your chosen appearance</td>
              <td>Until cleared</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2>What we don't use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>No tracking cookies</strong> — we do not use Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, or any third-party tracking</li>
          <li><strong>No advertising cookies</strong> — we do not serve ads or participate in ad networks</li>
          <li><strong>No cross-site cookies</strong> — we do not share data with third-party advertisers</li>
          <li><strong>No fingerprinting</strong> — we do not use browser fingerprinting techniques</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Third-party services</h2>
        <p>This site may load resources from the following external services:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> — to deliver typefaces used on the site. Google may set cookies as part of this service. See <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent-blue);">Google's privacy policy</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Gravatar</strong> — to display author profile images. See <a href="https://automattic.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent-blue);">Automattic's privacy policy</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to control cookies</h2>
        <p>You can control and delete cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>View and delete existing cookies</li>
          <li>Block cookies from specific or all websites</li>
          <li>Set preferences for certain types of cookies</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To clear the theme preference stored by this site, you can clear your browser's local storage for this domain, or use your browser's "Clear site data" option.</p>
        <p>For more information on managing cookies in your browser:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent-blue);">Google Chrome</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/clear-cookies-and-site-data-firefox" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent-blue);">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/en-gb/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent-blue);">Apple Safari</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent-blue);">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>If we add new cookies or tracking in the future, this page will be updated to reflect those changes. We recommend checking this page periodically.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this cookie policy, you can reach me at <a href="mailto:najcheski.hristijan@gmail.com" style="color: var(--color-accent-blue);">najcheski.hristijan@gmail.com</a> or via the <a href="/contact/" style="color: var(--color-accent-blue);">contact page</a>.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .policy-content {
      max-width: 760px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .policy-content h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: var(--text-xl);
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--color-text-primary);
      margin: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-3);
    }
    .policy-content h2:first-child {
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    .policy-content p {
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    }
    .policy-content ul {
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.8;
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    }
    .policy-content li {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    }
    .policy-content code {
      background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.9em;
    }
    .policy-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-6);
    }
    .policy-table th,
    .policy-table td {
      text-align: left;
      padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      font-size: var(--text-sm);
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    }
    .policy-table th {
      color: var(--color-text-primary);
      font-weight: 600;
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
